The game Wan Fu Cave Game is played by two players on a 5x5 rectangle board with square tiling. All players play with Markers. Rules for Pieces: Markers hop adjacent then if can move hop adjacent, move again or step adjacent. Players take turns moving. Setup: Place a Marker for player one at the union of the bottom sites of the board expanded by 1 steps and the vertexes with coordinates [D3, E3]. Place a Marker for player two at the union of the top sites of the board expanded by 1 steps and the vertexes with coordinates [A3, B3].. Rules: Move one of your pieces. Aim: If the next player cannot move, the next player loses If the number of pieces owned by Player 1 is less than or equal to 9, player one loses. The Wan Fu Cave Game (Ludii 1) ruleset.
